Almost every culture has its own blend of aromatic vegetables that make up a "sofrito" – our version uses carrot, onion, celery, and sweet bell pepper to give this dish its flavor base. A combination of both soft and crunchy veggies gives this dish textural pizazz, while spicy roasted tofu adds zip. A little fresh mint over top wakes up all the flavors!

Preheat oven to 425. Press the @tofu{1%block} between #paper towels{} to remove excess liquid, then slice into 1-inch cubes. Toss the cubed tofu on a #baking sheet{} with @salt{}, @pepper{}, @chili powder{1%tsp}, and @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Place in the oven and roast for ~{20-25%minutes}, until golden brown and crispy.

Meanwhile, halve, core, seed, and remove the white ribs from the @green bell pepper{1}(halved and deseeded), then finely dice. Peel the @carrots{1}. Mince half the carrot and half the @celery{1}, then cut the remaining carrot and celery into thin matchsticks. Cut the @sugar snap peas{8%oz} in half lengthwise on a diagonal. Halve, peel, and finely dice the @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Chop the @mint{1%sprig}(chopped).

== Sofrito ==

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a large #pan{} over medium heat. Add the diced onion, minced carrot, minced celery, and as much @chili flakes{1%tsp} as you dare and cook, tossing, for ~{5-6%minutes}, until very soft. Add the diced bell pepper to the pan and cook, stirring occasionally, another ~{5%minutes}, until soft and slightly caramelized. Season with salt and pepper.

Add the snap peas, carrot, celery, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and @water{1/2%cup} to the pan with the bell pepper mixture. Cook, tossing, for ~{3-4%minutes}, until vegetables are crisp-tender and sauce has thickened. Stir in half the mint and season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Toss the tofu into the sofrito and serve with a sprinkle of remaining mint. Enjoy!